CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 30, 1953, pg. 14, reads: "Jubilant Jabberwockies - Pittsburgh was treated to the best Jabberwock seen in these parted in many years, according to those who have taken part each year. A gay group of young folk pranced and danced and sang their way right into the hears of a capacity audience.  General chairman was Ardelle Douglass and working with her was a magnificent committee of Delta Sigma Theta sorors...Second photo: the Pittsburgh Junior Leaguers pranced gaily before the curtain in Prologue and Epilogue, bright as buttons in their lightening blue bellhop jackets and white skirts.  They were frankly adorable.  Left to right: Beverly Butler, Kay Stokes, Sarah Burney, Marva - Jo Hord, Sylvia Knott, Betsy Johnson and Bootsie Bray..."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Beverly Butler, Kay Stokes, Sarah Burney, Marva Jo Hord, Sylvia Knott, Betsy Johnson, and LouJeanne "Bootsie Bray" wearing satin bellhop jackets, light colored skirts, and tap shoes, posed in kick line on stage, for Delta Sigma Theta Sorority "Coronation Capers Jabberwock"
